The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Kotak Bank splits stock
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Kotak Bank splits stock
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                                             
	Mumbai, May 11: Kotak Mahindra Bank today opted for a stock split by sub-dividing its equity shares of face value of Rs 10 each to Rs 5 apiece.         
	The decision comes days after HDFC Ltd sub-divided the face value of its shares to Rs 2 each from Rs 10 apiece to increase retail participation.         
	Kotak Mahindra joins the growing list of companies who have recently announced a stock split.         
	Sterlite Industries, which brought down the face value of its share to Rs 1 from Rs 2, Engineers India Ltd and Jayshree Tea amp; Industries are a few companies to split their shares.         
	Kotak Mahindra Bank today reported a 99 per cent growth in consolidated net profit at Rs 418 crore for the quarter ended March 31 compared with Rs 211 crore in the corresponding period a year ago.         
	Total income increased to Rs 2,945 crore from Rs 2,232 crore in the year-ago period.         
	The banks consolidated advances as on March 31, 2010 stood at Rs 29,724 crore, a 32 per cent growth over Rs 22,498 crore a year ago.        
	Consolidated net interest margin for the year stood at 6.3 per cent, up from 6.1 per cent in the previous fiscal.         
	Deposits were up 53 per cent to Rs 23,886 crore from Rs 15,645 crore a year ago.         
	The bank said the low cost current account and saving account deposits constituted 31 per cent of the total deposits.        
	The companys board has proposed a dividend of Rs 0.85 per share of Rs 10 face value for the shareholders.         
	On the Bombay Stock Exchange, the Kotak Mahindra Bank scrip closed at Rs 745.30, down 2.09 per cent from its previous close.                                                                                                                                      
